Currently...I’m on the phone with the Ubereats driver who’s there to pick up an order at 10:00pm. It was placed at 7:49pm. I see a message saying that my order was delayed. The driver let’s them know she’s there to pick up the order and then asks if it’s ready. The worker gives her a sharp NO and then no additional info. Two seconds later I get a msg in the Uber Eats app saying that my order is canceled because it couldn’t be delivered. OH REALLY CALEXICO? How come it couldn’t be delivered when the driver was standing right there.  Listen it’s a pandemic and I get it. There are bigger things happening on this planet. But we could all use a little comfort right now. And after yet another long day of mothering, cleaning, and remote learning on repeat I just looked forward to this one little piece of comfort to go along with my taco Tuesday homemade margarita. So screw you Calexico for not even being decent enough to be honest and just say “sorry we f’d this one up”. It wasn’t a delivery problem. It was a YOU problem. PERIODT!
